For some of those allocations I can see that they use a special std::allocator. Does this mean they will be using memory pools in consecutive calls to ```session.Run(...)```?

For the next (second) iteration and call to ```session.Run(...)```, I get only 88 allocations, but also only 87 deallocations. So there seems to be one allocation leaking.
